for deputy director of central intelligence to reorganize the agency  with particular emphasis on covert activities psychological warfare and building a professional career agency jackson was appointed deputy director of the central intelligence agency on august   and swornin october  he was the first deputy director of central intelligence ddci to serve under former ambassador to the soviet union – and former world war ii fourstar general walter bedell smith dci smith and jackson brought allen w dulles to cia under contract as deputy directorplans clandestine activities in early  after completing the reorganization in accordance with adoption of the dulles report and nsc and jacksons resignation in august  allen dulles was promoted to ddci to replace jackson later replacing smith as dci in  jackson remained a contract special adviser to the dci through both the smith and dulles directorships during the eisenhower administration bill jackson is listed by the white house staff publication and by the cia as being a special adviser and senior consultant to the director of central intelligence from – in  jackson was appointed chairman of president eisenhowers committee on international information activities often known inside the beltway as the jackson committee  which led to creation of the us information agency usia in december  jackson resigned from j h whitney  co and was named special assistant to the secretary of state john foster dulles to attend the  big four talks in geneva in february  jackson was appointed special assistant to president eisenhower on psychological warfare succeeding nelson rockefeller jackson served briefly as united states national security adviser from september   until january   personal lifeedit jacksons first wife elizabeth lyman married  was the exwife of thomas rice of dover she brought two children thomas rice jr and lyman rice to their marriage jackson and elizabeth had two more sons william harding jackson jr and richard lee jackson they divorced in  after jackson returned from world war ii at age  jackson was elected the youngest president to serve  on the board of directors of the society of the new york hospital one of americas oldest hospitals founded by king george iii in  and was nominated to the national academy of sciences after the war jackson was elected to the boards of bankers trust the john hay whitney foundation the new york hospital for special surgery and the menninger foundation in  jackson married mary pitcairn the daughter of norman b pitcairn a former president of the wabash railroad they had two sons together bruce p jackson and howell e jackson after they divorced around  keating married another new york lawyer wendell davis who died in  she married a third time to us senator and former ambassador to israel kenneth keating thus becoming mary pitcairn jackson davis keating deathedit jackson died on september   in tucson arizona at age  he is interred at mount olivet cemetery in nashville tennessee referencesedit  a b c william h jackson dead at  former cia deputy director new york times september     a b reference the central intelligence agency by arthur b darling copyright  isbn   and general walter bedell smith as director of central intelligence by ludwell lee montague copyright  isbn   both texts declassified with redactions and deletions by the cia and published by the pennsylvania state university press  reference tennessee state library and archives the papers of william hicks jackson from  accession number  completed december    ellis francis m clark edward f jr  a brief history of carter ledyard  milburn new york ny peter e randall oclc    national archives and records administration college park md rgoss stack  row  compartment  shelf  box  oss personnel file  colonel william harding jackson  omar n bradley and clay blair  a generals life an autobiography by general of the amy omar n bradley new york ny simon  schuster  new york pp – isbn    nara rgoss office o